\dilIt is... certainly unfortunate that I
am bound to this tree. Coming down to the
Overworld was the only way to continue
defending the World Tree, but still...
Dilong
\dil...confinement to your destiny is still confinement.
Dilong
\dilHow I wish I could roam free again, free
to observe the Overworld, free to do as I
wish, free to be safe with my queen Trailia...
but this is my lifelong duty, no matter what.
Dilong
\dilAs long as I know I am keeping the World Tree safe,
I am content with resting here for eternity. Yet... I
do have the desire to be able to watch the adventure of
the four who have just bested me in combat.
Dilong
\dilI suppose that if they manage to right
the wrongs of what happened eons ago, I
may finally be able to once again see the
natural world I have spent so long defending.

Dilong
\dilI am Dilong, the Dragon of Nature, and a member
of the group you humans call the Immortals.
Dilong
\dilI welcome you four to the peak of the World Tree.
Dilong
\dilIn the past, I've seen many a group of adventurers
fight through the gauntlets prior to their encounter
with me. After all that... I always stand as their
final challenge, the last hurdle on their great climb.
Dilong
\dilIt's unfortunate that all of them have
come with bad intent in mind, isn't it?
Dilong
\dilSome of those adventuers worship that
damned \c[30]soul\c[0] of the Fallen One, hoping to
somehow strike me down and advance their
wicked agenda.
Dilong
\dilSome of them even come expecting great
treasures, and before I end their sorry
lives, I always ask them... why?
Dilong
\dilWhy would you think there are riches here?
The World Tree and Lost Forest are untouchable
by man-made, unnatural constructs. Treasure
has no place here.
Dilong
\dilThis tree only stands here to provide
life to the Overworld... without it,
only the undead may reign over this land.
Dilong
\dilBut that brings me to the question
of you four. What brings you here?
Actor4
\p3Dilong... I... first of all, I am beyond
honored to be in your presence. But trust
me when I say we come with no mal intent.
Actor4
\p3I am a cleric devoted to my worship of
Trailia, and I would never dare do such
a thing as show any good spirit towards
anything that may endanger the world.
Actor4
\p3In fact, we've come here to accomplish
just the opposite. We need a piece of
a golden tablet in order to break the
seal on a door underneath Telluria Castle.
Actor4
\p3We think \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] is down
there, and even if he's not... this
is our only lead, and we need to try.
Dilong
\dilAh yes, this tablet piece... the only
exception to the tree's pureness.
Dilong
\dilTrust me when I say I want to believe you.
I want to lose a fight to the right people.
I want to find a worthy group of adventurers
that may bring us closer to freedom.
Dilong
\dilBut as I am bound to this tree, I am
unable to observe anything that happens
outside it or the Lost Forest.
Dilong
\dilFor all I know, you four could be carrying
a wisp of the Fallen One's \c[30]soul\c[0], hoping to
infect me and this tree and bring an end to
nature as we know it. Wouldn't be the first time.
Dilong
\dilFor all I know, you four could be
stupid, greedy travelers, hoping to
find a pinch of gold up here.
Dilong
\dilFor all I know... maybe you four
really are pure of heart and soul,
and you, the cleric, are not lying.

Dilong
\dilI suppose that our battle shall be the test of that.
Dilong
\dilEnough talking; fight me, adventurers!
For I, Dilong, the Dragon of Nature, with
the powers of earth, wind, and light endowed
to me, will not hold back my judgement!

Dilong
\dilAs guardian of the World Tree, I am the defender
of the Overworld's life and spirit. Still, I am not
the only obstacle in the paths of those who choose
to reach the summit of this grand structure.
Dilong
\dilWithout the Lost Forest and the creatures
who live in this mountain-boxed stretch of
land, many a traveler in bad spirits would
have no trouble reaching where we stand now.
Dilong
\dilOr even worse... the evil forces of
\c[18]Apocalypse\c[0], during any of the
times he has destroyed your civilization.
Dilong
\dilBut now, for the first time ever, a group
of adventurers has bested me in combat.
Dilong
\dilI'm almost certain of it. With the power
you possess now, you four are right on track
to be the one's who seal the Fallen One's
\c[30]soul\c[0] once and for all.
Actor4
\p3Dilong... thank you. Thank you for that amazing
battle, and thank you for honoring us with your
holy presence. And now, I don't mean to be rude,
but... what about that tablet piece?
Dilong
\dilAh, no worries about being rude. Although you
may only be mortals, I consider us equals now.
CAM EVENT 5 1600
Dilong
\dilA millenium ago, a single mage entered
the Lost Forest and called to me. He did
not wish to go any further, but simply asked
me to guard a half of a golden tablet.
Dilong
\dilHe said nothing else, and the tablet had no abnormal
magical presence, so I accepted, simply because of his
respect and the horrors I know have been happening across
the Overworld for as long as I've been here.
Dilong
\dilBut you say that it will break the lock
on a door that is sealing \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0]
himself... I assume both tablet pieces must
be combined in order to gain its full power.
Dilong
\dilOf course I will allow you four to pass
and take this tablet piece, you deserve it.
CAM EVENT 17 1600
Dilong
\dilBut if that mage came here a millenium
ago... that means the clock is ticking for
Apocalypse's next strike. There isn't much
time until the Great Collapse repeats itself.
Dilong
\dilIn that case, you will also need this.
Adventuers, I grant you my blessing:
Dilong
\dilThat will aid you in the battles to come.
Actor4
\p3Dilong, thank you so much for everything.
But... I have some questions. How are you
down here if the ties between the Overworld
and the Above have been apparently severed?
Dilong
\dilThe ties being severed means nothing more
than the fact that we can no longer cross
between the planes and are bound to specific
locations in the Overworld.
Dilong
\dilLet's just say that when the Fallen One
was banished, he was not the only one to
cross the gap.
Actor4
\p3Wha... so you're saying...
Dilong
\dilYes, I am not the only other Immortal in
the Overworld at the moment. If you are on
the path to seal that \c[30]evil spirit\c[0], you
will certainly encounter more of us.
Dilong
\dilI understand that you must have many more
questions, but bombarding you with information
will only serve to confuse you and lead you
down the wrong path. You will learn eventually.
Dilong
\dilI must rest now, and you four must return
to Telluria Castle to prepare for whatever
comes next. Best of luck with everything.
Actor4
\p3Dilong! Will we ever meet again?
Dilong
\dilIt depends. Us Immortals cannot leave
our designated areas that we watch over...
but I'm sure that we will see each other
at least once more before this is all over.
